div.p:
Multiplicatis his integralibus per coefficientes seriei integrandae 1\textrm{,
            }\frac{1}{1}\textrm{, }\frac{1}{1\cdot2}\textrm{, }\frac{1}{1\cdot2\cdot3}\textrm{,
            }\frac{1}{1\cdot2\cdot3\cdot4}, etc. positisque in linea verticali quae ad
          singulos pertinent terminos, orientur series infinitae, quae in unam summam collectae
          dabunt \int x^{x}dx, quod desiderabatur, illae autem series ita se
          habent
